#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1436
#, no-c-format
msgid "Zeroconf Error"
msgstr "Erro do Zeroconf"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1438
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&smb4k; uses the Zeroconf service (<application><ulink url=\"https://avahi."
"org\">Avahi</ulink></application>) to look up servers and shares in the "
"network neighborhood using DNS Service Discovery (DNS-SD). For this to work, "
"the Avahi daemon must be enabled and running on your system. If this is not "
"the case, &smb4k; shows an error message:"
msgstr ""
"O &smb4k; usa o serviço Zeroconf (<application><ulink url=\"https://avahi.org"
"\">Avahi</ulink></application>) para procurar pelos servidores e partilhas "
"na vizinhança da rede, usando a Descoberta de Serviços por DNS (DNS-SD). "
"Para isto funcionar, o serviço Avahi precisa de estar activado e em execução "
"no seu sistema. Se não for o caso, o &smb4k; mostra uma mensagem de erro:"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: index.docbook:1441
#, no-c-format
msgid "Screenshot of the Zeroconf error notification"
msgstr "Imagem da notificação do erro do Zeroconf"

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:1444
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Zeroconf error notification"
msgstr "A notificação do erro do Zeroconf"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1448
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In most cases, the Avahi daemon is not running when an error is reported. "
"Under those &Linux; distributions that use <application>systemd</"
"application> you can start it by running the following or a similar command "
"from the terminal:"
msgstr ""
"Na maioria dos casos, o serviço do Avahi não está em execução quando é "
"apresentado um erro. Nas distribuições de &Linux; que usam o "
"<application>systemd</application>, poderá iniciar o mesmo, executando o "
"seguinte comando no terminal (ou outro equivalente):"

#. Tag: screen
#: index.docbook:1449
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput><prompt>$</prompt> <command>sudo</command> <command>systemctl</"
"command> enable --now avahi-daemon</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput><prompt>$</prompt> <command>sudo</command> <command>systemctl</"
"command> enable --now avahi-daemon</userinput>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1450
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With all other &Linux; distributions and under BSD refer to the specific "
"documentation how to start the Avahi daemon."
msgstr ""
"Com as outras distribuições de &Linux; e no BSD, veja a documentação "
"específica sobre como iniciar o servidor Avahi."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1458
#, no-c-format
msgid "Denied Privilege Escalation"
msgstr "Proibição da Escalada de Privilégios"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1460
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In case the mount and unmount actions fail (most likely with an "
"<guilabel>AuthorizationDeniedError</guilabel> message), your polkit-1 setup "
"might need to be adjusted: Add a file, &eg; named <filename>10-mounthelper."
"rules</filename>, to the <filename class=\"directory\">$PREFIX/etc/polkit-1/"
"rules.d/</filename> directory with the following content:"
msgstr ""
"No caso de as acções de montagem e desmontagem falharem com um erro "
"<guilabel>AuthorizationDeniedError</guilabel>, a sua configuração do "
"'polkit-1' poderá ter de ser ajustada: Adicione um ficheiro, &eg; chamado "
"<filename>10-mounthelper.rules</filename>, à pasta <filename class="
"\"directory\">$PREFIX/etc/polkit-1/rules.d/</filename> com o seguinte "
"conteúdo:"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:1462
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"polkit.addRule(function(action, subject) {\n"
"        if (action.id == \"org.kde.smb4k.mounthelper.mount\" &amp;&amp; \n"
"            subject.isInGroup(\"wheel\")) {\n"
"                return polkit.Result.YES;\n"
"        }\n"
"});\n"
"\n"
"polkit.addRule(function(action, subject) {\n"
"        if (action.id == \"org.kde.smb4k.mounthelper.unmount\" &amp;&amp;\n"
"            subject.isInGroup(\"wheel\")) {\n"
"                return polkit.Result.YES;\n"
"        }\n"
"});"
msgstr ""
"polkit.addRule(function(action, subject) {\n"
"        if (action.id == \"org.kde.smb4k.mounthelper.mount\" &amp;&amp; \n"
"            subject.isInGroup(\"wheel\")) {\n"
"                return polkit.Result.YES;\n"
"        }\n"
"});\n"
"\n"
"polkit.addRule(function(action, subject) {\n"
"        if (action.id == \"org.kde.smb4k.mounthelper.unmount\" &amp;&amp;\n"
"            subject.isInGroup(\"wheel\")) {\n"
"                return polkit.Result.YES;\n"
"        }\n"
"});"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1464
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This allows all users in the Unix group <emphasis>wheel</emphasis> to "
"execute the mount and unmount actions. You may adjust the group of "
"authorized users to any group you prefer to use (&eg; <emphasis>sudo</"
"emphasis> or <emphasis>operator</emphasis>)."
msgstr ""
"Isto permite que todos os utilizadores no grupo de UNIX <emphasis>wheel</"
"emphasis> executem a acção de montagem e desmontagem. Poderá ajustar o grupo "
"de utilizadores autorizados com qualquer grupo que necessitar (&eg; "
"<emphasis>sudo</emphasis> ou <emphasis>operator</emphasis>)."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:1472
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mounting Problems Under BSD"
msgstr "Problemas de Montagem no BSD"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1474
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "If mounting of password-protected shares from either a &Samba; or a "
#| "&Windows; server fails, this might be because <ulink url=\"man:/"
#| "mount_smbfs\"><citerefentry><refentrytitle>mount_smbfs</"
#| "refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></citerefentry></ulink> only uses "
#| "NTLMv1 authentication, and the server does not support it. To fix "
#| "mounting for a &Samba; server, you can add the following entry to the "
#| "[global] section of the <filename>smb.conf</filename> file of "
#| "<emphasis>the server</emphasis>:"
msgid ""
"If mounting of shares from either a &Samba; or a &Windows; server fails, "
"this might be because <ulink url=\"man:/mount_smbfs"
"\"><citerefentry><refentrytitle>mount_smbfs</refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</"
"manvolnum></citerefentry></ulink> only uses NTLMv1 authentication and "
"requires the SMB 1.0/&CIFS; protocol, and the server does not support those. "
"To fix mounting for a &Samba; server, you can add the following entries to "
"the [global] section of the <ulink url=\"man:/smb.conf"
"\"><citerefentry><refentrytitle><filename>smb.conf</filename></"
"refentrytitle><manvolnum>5</manvolnum></citerefentry></ulink> file of "
"<emphasis>the server</emphasis>:"
msgstr ""
"Se falhar a montagem das partilhas protegidas por senha de um servidor de "
"&Samba; ou &Windows;, isto poder-se-á dever ao facto de que o <ulink url="
"\"man:/mount_smbfs\"><citerefentry><refentrytitle>mount_smbfs</"
"refentrytitle><manvolnum>8</manvolnum></citerefentry></ulink> só usa a "
"autenticação em NTLMv1 e o servidor não a suporta. Para corrigir a montagem "
"para um servidor de &Samba; poderá adicionar o seguinte elemento à secção "
"[global] do ficheiro <filename>smb.conf</filename> do <emphasis>servidor</"
"emphasis>:"

#. Tag: programlisting
#: index.docbook:1476
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "[global]\n"
#| "...\n"
#| "ntlm auth = yes\n"
#| "..."
msgid ""
"[global]\n"
"...\n"
"ntlm auth = yes\n"
"server min protocol = NT1\n"
"..."
msgstr ""
"[global]\n"
"...\n"
"ntlm auth = yes\n"
"..."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1478
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "To fix this issue for a &Windows; server, please contact the sysadmin and "
#| "tell her or him that NTLMv1 authentication should be swtiched on (if "
#| "possible)."
msgid ""
"If you want to fix this issue for a &Windows; server, please contact the "
"sysadmin and tell her or him that NTLMv1 authentication and the SMB 1.0/"
"&CIFS; protocol should be switched on (if possible)."
msgstr ""
"Para corrigir este problema para um servidor &Windows;, contacte por favor o "
"administrador de sistemas e diga-lhe que a autenticação NTLMv1 deverá ser "
"activada (se possível)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:1480
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is not advisable to enable the SMB 1.0/&CIFS; protocol on a server, "
"because it is considered insecure (see &eg; <ulink url=\"https://"
"techcommunity.microsoft.com/t5/storage-at-microsoft/stop-using-smb1/ba-"
"p/425858\">here</ulink>) and was thus disabled in newer &Samba; and "
"&Windows; versions (see &eg; <ulink url=\"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/"
"archive/blogs/josebda/the-deprecation-of-smb1-you-should-be-planning-to-get-"
"rid-of-this-old-smb-dialect\">here</ulink> and <ulink url=\"https://www."
"samba.org/samba/history/samba-4.11.0.html\">here</ulink>)."
msgstr ""

